<div class="header2">Peer Reviewers</div><br />
<div style="width:600px">
 The MHLP  selects two peer reviewers for each article it publishes. Selection of peer  reviewers is made based on the fit between their area(s) of expertise and the  subject matter of the article. The evaluation of articles is double-blind, and  is based on originality, argumentation, clarity of thesis, quality of language,  correctness of references to past scholarship, and importance of the article to  the field. Peer reviewers of Forum commentaries will also consider the quality  of the interpretation of the MHLP article commented upon.
  <p>Peer  reviewers are requested to return their reviews within three weeks of receiving  the article. </p>
  <p>To  volunteer as a peer reviewer for the MHLP, please email the Publication at <a href="mailto:editor.mhlp@mail.mcgill.ca">editor.mhlp@mail.mcgill.ca</a> to express your interest. A directory of scholars who are willing to volunteer  their time is kept on file. We thank you for helping to advance health law  scholarship. </p>
    <p>You can download the  peer reviewer guidelines by <a href="documents/Peer Reviewer Guidelines MHLP en.doc">clicking here</a>.</p>
